annotation.TEXT: Anyway, take the lower path at this set of pipes.
Yeah, those koopduders can live.
I hope I don't run out of hearts...
Alright, for 6-4, I'll be going with a random Simon skin.
Wow, that transition to the Zelda II battle theme was nearly perfect!
It helps if I throw in the correct direction, of course.
Well, it didn't give a pop-up tutorial message, but I believe this is the Magma Bazooka from Mega Man 9, which is a chargeable 3-way fireball weapon.
Meh. That one can live.
Yeah, I'm not gonna bother with every single coin here.
I think maybe if I double jump just right...
And that's game! And I have no idea what he turned into, but whatever!
Whoa, I know you like to climb walls and ceilings, but don't go nuts now.
Oh, right. This level has two power ups, which seems unusually generous for The Lost Levels, since the only X-3 level with two power ups in the original SMB is 8-3.

Hmm... I wonder if that's the fire bar that supposedly "jumps" straight onto the player? Hmm.. Maybe it only screws over players choosing the middle route there (which isn't the right route anyway, but players shouldn't get auto-fried just for going the wrong way).
Ooh, lucky break there.
Sophia is really good for underwater levels.
Bah, maybe not. That stinks... Wait, maybe I can get to it from the other side... Oh, and watch out for the poison that's in one of these blocks as well.
Wait, can I grab it using my boomerang?
And here I rescue some guy (no, not me).
Yeah, I should certainly be able to get up there from this side.
I'll just use my double jump to help me across this gap.
And, likewise, I'm not gonna bother seeing what the pipe skipped to my left here. (There's nothing interesting over there anyway.)
Okay, I'm back. Fortunately, it doesn't look like there were any audio desyncs as a result of me pausing the recording there this time.
Perfect!
Now, just like in past water levels, there are places where I can go over the top, above the water. But, as usual, I'll stay down here.
Gotcha! The magical boomerang is mine! I'm glad I thought of that!
It seems weird that the Zelda II final boss music would be used for invincibility here, but whatever. There's a lot of unusual music choices in Crossover.
Now, for 6-3, I could go with either Mario, Link, or Bill. Well, I think I've been overusing Bill lately, so not him this time.
Oh, man! It's a battle of throwing arc weapons!
There's a power up here, which Skull Man definitely wants.
Maybe not... Unless maybe I'm point-blank when I shoot it.
Alt. skin votes include ULTIMATE NINJA GUY (Haggleman (Ryu)), Tetrimino (Sophia), NES Link, NES Samus, Skull Man (Bass), and BS LoZ's Zelda.
And, just like at the end of other underground or underwater levels, there's a couple of hidden coin blocks in front of the flagpole.
Whoa, that was risky! Okay, the parakoopa's out of the question, but what about the cheepos? Well, I'd have to get very lucky, I think...
To be continued... Yo!
Alright, it's boss time, against... Who or what is that? I have no idea.
Music change signals low time, but this guy should be just about dead...
Alright! Oh, and assuming I can aim my weapon right, I can hit these two coin blocks above the pipe that the plumbers wouldn't be able to hit without exploiting a glitch.
Yeah, that thing's a Buzzy, but since I stunned it with the block, I can kick it-- Whoa!
I got a monochrome version of Dracula X's Richter, it looks like.
Umm... One moment, please. I got interrupted by something in the real world.
Okay, let's hope Richter doesn't get unlucky with Bowser's fireballs like Mario did back in 4-4...
Now, in this row of ? blocks is a power up, but I don't know if I'll be able to reach it...
There wasn't a Dracula X for the Game Boy, was there?
And, I want to take the lower path here as well. I'll do another double jump to get across the tiny gap along the way.
Cool! Now I've got the stronger arrows for Zelda to use!
I'm not gonna bother hunting down every fish this time.
Yeah, there's a multi-coin block there, but there's no way I'm going to get a lot of coins from it since I'm busy battling this guy.
I choose Link, and I'll go with the Zelda skin from BS Legend of Zelda.
Alright, now for 6-2, as requested, I'll use the Tetrimino! And, since I used the NES version last time I used it, I'll go with the SNES version this time.
What, I wasn't high enough to get 5000? Well, at least I got the six fireworks.
Yo, hammer dude, could you jump down here so I can shoot you? Thanks.

Yeah, I gotta remember that kicked shells won't go down gaps like that in Crossover for some dumb reason (I remember how Quick Man got quick-killed because of that back in LL 2-4!). Now, over here is a star and a hidden 1-up. Just watch out for the parakoopa.
I think I'll downthrust during most of my jumps, just in case.
Finally got him. Okay, for the next proper route, I think you need to take the top path here.
I need one to fly just the right way...
Oh, man. If I recall correctly... Yep, this level's got flying cheepos!
I've gotta be careful, since I don't have any weapons that can damage Bullet Bills right now.
Um, nope. I should dash jump.
That could've gotten sketchy, but my homing missiles helped me out there.

Anyway, this is another one of those "maze" castles, and the first proper route you need to take is under that fire bar, which is normally a super-long one, but I imagine it was shrunk there so that slower characters could get past it in time.
Hmm... They don't seem that much stronger, although they do tear through Cheep-Cheeps. Of course, those fish are weak enough to be one-shotted by Zelda's sword anyway.
Time's running out, so I'm not gonna bother with some of the coins here.

Also, voters wanted me to use Sophia for 6-2, Mario, Link, and Bill for 6-3, and Simon for 6-4. 6-1 didn't receive any specific votes, so I think I'll go with Skull Man here, since he hasn't seen much action.
So, arrows are stronger and sword attacks are weaker. Too bad I don't have arrows right now...
Man, I really want those hearts there, but it's too risky to go for them right now.
I think some of these ledges were extended to help weaker jumpers, and I can now hit this ? block more easily. However, its power up is too high to jump to...
Oh, well. The arrows are still nice to have. They might come in handy in the future, assuming I can get out of this level without getting hurt...
Hello, and welcome back to more SMB Crossover! Up above are the voting results this time.
Alright, I'd say today went well, since I didn't take any damage, not even from the cheepos! I did kind of spend most of Richter's hearts during 6-4, but that beats getting hurt or dying, I'd say.
Here's an underwater bonus room... Maybe my new Magma Bazooka will come in handy here.
I definitely will want my homing missiles ready.

Okay, whew. Those fire bars didn't screw me over during their little "jump" there. I remember reading in the ER forums about a fire bar in this level "jumping" directly on top of a player at one point.
Hiyah! The wall climb ability lets me slip through that gap!
Yeah, being point-blank helps, so that more than one fireball can hit the target.
Alright, there's the goal. Now, can I make it to the flagpole without royally screwing up somehow?
And, as usual, those blocks make getting 5000 and six fireworks a piece of cake, which is not a lie!
So, which of these duders should I use for world 7? Vote now!
